    <text id="R119283122T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>During the battle of Antietam, Chambersburg played an important role in supplying
                    Union forces. In this letter, General McClellan asks Ordnance Chief James Ripley
                    to send Parrott artillery ammunition through Chambersburg to the front.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. ARMY OF THE POTOMAC,
                    <name type="recipient">Brig.-Gen. RIPLEY,<lb/> Chief of Ordnance:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-09-17">September 17, 1862. (Received 10 p. m.)</date>
                        <name type="place">Via Hagerstown, Md.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>If you can possibly do it, force some 20-pounder Parrott ammunition through
                    to-night, via Hagerstown and Chambersburg, to us, near Sharpsburg, Md.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>GEO. B. MCCLELLAN,<lb/> Maj. Gen., Cmdg.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
